   Program Summary: Program Direction

   Vision Statement
   Pest management for a sustainable agriculture

   Mission Statement
   To provide technology to manage pest populations below economic damage
   thresholds by the integration of environmentally compatible strategies
   that are based on increased understanding of the biology and ecology of
   insect, mite, and weed pests.

   Research Components

   A.  Insects and Mites
     * Identification and Classification of Insects and Mites
     * Biology of Pests and Natural Enemies (includes microbes)
     * Plant, Pest, and Natural Enemy Interactions and Ecology
     * Postharvest, Pest Exclusion, and Quarantine Treatment
     * Pest Control Technologies
     * Integrated Pest Management Systems and Areawide Suppression
       Programs

   B.  Weed Science
     * Weed Biology and Ecology
     * Chemical Control of Weeds
     * Biological Control of Weeds
     * Weed Management Systems
